# Root Cause Analysis

## Trigger chain

The issue is in `load_initial_state()` in `crates/kanban-tui/src/app/mod.rs` (~line 1585):

```rust
async fn load_initial_state(&mut self) {
    if self.persistence.save_file.is_some() {
        let store = self.ctx.store().clone();
        if store.exists().await {
            // ... loads data from file ...
        }
        // store does NOT exist — falls through
    }
    self.migrate_sprint_logs(); // ALWAYS called, even on empty/missing store
    self.check_ended_sprints();
    // ...
}
```

`migrate_sprint_logs()` always calls `execute_command`:

```rust
// crates/kanban-tui/src/app/mod.rs ~line 1940
fn migrate_sprint_logs(&mut self) {
    let cmd = Box::new(kanban_domain::commands::MigrateSprintLogs);
    if let Err(e) = self.ctx.execute_command(cmd) {
        tracing::error!("Failed to migrate sprint logs: {}", e);
    }
}
```

`TuiContext::execute_commands_batch` unconditionally queues a snapshot save:

```rust
// crates/kanban-tui/src/tui_context.rs ~line 59
pub fn execute_commands_batch(&mut self, commands: Vec<Box<dyn Command>>) -> KanbanResult<()> {
    self.inner.execute(commands)?;
    let snapshot = self.inner.snapshot();
    self.save_coordinator.queue_snapshot(snapshot); // always queued
    Ok(())
}
```

And `KanbanContext::execute` always marks dirty:

```rust
// crates/kanban-service/src/context.rs ~line 180
pub fn execute(&mut self, commands: Vec<Box<dyn Command>>) -> KanbanResult<()> {
    self.history.capture_before_command(self.snapshot());
    for command in commands { /* ... */ }
    self.dirty = true; // always set, even for no-op commands
    Ok(())
}
```

So even with no boards, `migrate_sprint_logs()` queues an empty snapshot write, which the save worker flushes to disk — creating `kanban.json`.

## Why the file watcher error appears

File watching is initialized in `App::run()` after `load_initial_state()` but before the save worker runs. Since `kanban.json` doesn't exist yet, `start_watching` fails with `ENOENT`:

```rust
// crates/kanban-tui/src/app/mod.rs ~line 1601
if let Some(ref save_file) = self.persistence.save_file {
    let watcher = kanban_persistence::FileWatcher::new();
    let path = std::path::PathBuf::from(save_file);
    if let Err(e) = watcher.start_watching(path.clone()).await {
        tracing::warn!("Failed to start file watching for {}: {}", path.display(), e);
    }
}
```

